    TweetComments (0)
                                    Please log in to add your comment.
                                Report abuseTranscript of ARAMARK ARAMARKARAMARK The industry of ARAMARK is an American food service, facilities, and clothing provider supplying for businesses, educational institutions, sport facilities, federal & state prisons, and health care institutions. It's headquarters is located in Center City, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. It's global reach is that they service in 22 different counties including: US, Canada, Spain, Chile, Ireland, United Kingdom, and Germany. A unique fact about ARAMARK is that a company-wide volunteer initiative started in 2007 to help families in need. THE MARKETING STRATEGY AND PLANNING PROCESS ARAMARK'S VISION THE MARKETING STRATEGY AND PLANNING PROCESSARAMARK'S dominate strategy E-COMMERCE AND THE GLOBAL MARKETING ENVIRONMENTIMPACT OF E-COMMERCE AND SOCIAL MEDIA E-COMMERCE AND THE GLOBAL MARKETING ENVIRONMENTCOMPLETE INDUSTRY STRUCTURE ANALYSIS Team ARAMARK Laura Taylor - A43850101 Andrew Schubert - A44215319Steven Bryndza - A43661641John Stando - A44690193Xingcan Chen - A45656907CORE VALUESThe core values of ARAMARK are to have a professional service organization that is dedicated to excellence. They want to manage service and manage the best. ARAMARK has high level on integrity to the community. They contribute to the community and nutrition to their customers. ARAMARK focuses on engaging competence, commitment and creativity of their people. BUSINESS DEFINITIONARAMARK's business definition is to develop and sustain the leadership position by engaging and supporting their most valuable and differentiated assets, competence, commitment, and creativity for the customers. They want to exceed the expectations of all customers. ARAMARK wants to do this by dedicating their skills in professional service. They create long term value and capture the greatest opportunity for all stakeholders. STRATEGIC DIRECTIONThe strategic direction of ARAMARK is to lead further in developing its facilities, uniform, and career capabilities through key acquisitions. They want to move and expand their facilities across the globe. STRATEGIC INFRASTRUCTURE The strategic infrastructure of ARAMARK is to focus on the people and customer system by focusing their business on the connection with the consumers. They also have a core value of information system by wanting to have a competitive advantage in expanding and growing. The SBU's is that ARAMARK has many difference services like food, facility, and uniform. Main dominate strategy: Customer IntimacyARAMARK wants to have long-term value with their customers. They want to build their products through their customers and they want to satisfy them. ARAMARK considers and addresses  issues that matter most to clients, customers, employees, and communitiesLow cost and DifferentiationARAMARK address differentiation by engaging and supporting the valuables and assets, competence, commitment, and creativity that appeal to each individual customers. ARMARAK focuses on low cost by having bulk supply for industries like colleges and prisons to appeal to a variety of customers. ARAMARK'S E-COMMERCEARAMARK uses an e-commerce portal that engages the community on campus. This is done by providing a campus dining program that allows a OneCard system. This provides information like nutrition, meal plans, and eating options. ARAMARK also engages in Twitter and Facebook to keep in touch with customers and employers. COMPETITIVE ADVANTAGE WITH ARAMARK'S E-COMMERCEARAMARK can sell items online, which is convenient for customers, and they can communicate to customers easier through social media allowing them to reach a broader customer base.  They are also technologically savvy, which appeals to college students. ARAMARK'S CLOUD COMPUTINGARAMARK engages in cloud computing by listing any job openings to people on the web. They also  increase efficiency in B2B transactions to suppliers. With the cloud computing, ARAMARK can engage with businesses they supply to online so they can access the suppliers more efficient and effectively. RIVALRY AMOUNG EXISTING FIRMSSome rivalries among existing firms for ARAMARK are: Compass GroupSodexoCintasPOTENTIAL ENTRANTSThe threat of potential entrants is on ARAMARK's radar. Since they have a large global scope, other companies can focus on a regional scope that can possibly steal some market share. SUPPLIERSARAMARK's suppliers are: National Urban League Diversity Inc. CongresoCatalystWomen's Food Service ForumUpward Synergy Out and Equal Human Rights CompainINTERMEDIARIES & BUYERSSome intermediaries and buyers include: Healthcare institutionsUniversities and schoolsGrocery storesStadiums and ArenasFacilities ManagementExamples of companies include:American Indian College PA-NJ-DECongreso SUBSTITUTESARAMARK's substitutes include : Local vendorsRegional suppliersCatering companiesLocal restaurants MARKETING INFORMATION AND RESEARCH SPECIFIC MARKETING RESEARCH AREAS#1 What kind of food does ARAMARK want to focus on? ARAMARK could conduct a focus group to a portion of their consumers to see what food they like, how much they would spend on that food, and if they would rather have packed lunches or buy ARAMARK's food. #2 How to figure out where to start with location and consumers?#3 Which of ARAMARK's services are used most?Surveys could be used to find out which of ARAMARK's services are used most. This will allow the company to become the leader of that specific industry. Also, ARAMARK could use growth data to determine which industries are trending and put more time to perfect that industry.MARKETING INFORMATION AND RESEARCH MARKETING RESEARCH PROCESS SELECTED AREAWhat kind of food should ARAMARK focus on? PROBLEM DEFINITIONSecondary research was conducted in order to figure out the problem of location and income for students and teachers. The over-weight issues and what food to serve is also ARAMARK's attraction of research. EXPLORATORY RESEARCH DESGINARAMARK did a focus group with three difference teachers and six students to see how much they were willing to pay for food and what kind of food they were attracted to. QUANTITATIVE RESEARCH DESIGNARAMARK provided a survey to their consumers to allow any feedback on the service of the company and about the types of food people enjoyed or did not like. UNDERSTANDING CONSUMER BEHAVIORPSYCHOLOGICAL FACTOR: PerceptionPSYCHOLOGICAL FACTOR: AttitudesConsumers will form attitudes about nutrition, quality, and trendiness for the food they consumer. ARAMARK's food services must coincide with the consumers attitudes about the food.IDEA TO POSITIVELY INFLUENCE CONSUMER BEHAVIOR ARAMARK could create an advertisement in which a football game is being played, and some fans are eating food in the stadium that is provided by ARAMARK.  Suppliers could learn about this company through classical conditioning, in which every time they see a football game being played, they think of ARAMARK.  This could positively influence suppliers' behavior of buying from ARAMARK.CREATING CUSTOMER SATISFACTION AND LOYALTY ARAMARK'S SATISFACTION AND LOYALTY ARAMARK creates satisfaction and loyalty by focusing their attention of the specific needs and wants of the customers. ARAMARK personally designs each product to the customers wants. With this personal attention on their customers, ARAMARK builds trust with each customer. ARAMARK'S CUSTOMER SATISFACTION SCORES ARAMARK won two awards related to their customer satisfaction such as:Gold Uniform Supplier award in Food Process magazine 2010 Reader's Choice2009 Hormel Foods "Spirit of Excellence" award.These awards correlates to ARAMARK's high success rates with their customers and suppliers. SOURCE: www.aramark.com CUSTOMER SATISFACTION AND LOYALTY PLAN FOR ARAMARK IDEA: In order to improve satisfaction and loyalty, ARAMARK could have a rewards card.IMPLEMENTATION PLAN: With this rewards card, ARAMARK customers will be able to get "points" when purchasing products with them. After they get a certain amount of points, the customers could get 50% off on the next order. This will make loyal customers stay and be satisfied when receiving this discount. SEGMENTATION, TARGETING AND POSITIONINGMAJOR TARGET MARKET SEGMENTS #1 Sports Arenas/ EntertainmentARAMARK has a 32 second spot titled "Sports". It describes how being apart of something bigger than yourself is great. Their ending phrase "great things happen when you put on a uniform," creates a relationship between their service and sports teams.#2 EducationARAMARK is a leading provider of dining, facilities, and conference center management to colleges across the country.#3 Retail outletsARAMARK describes a large selection of products to customers with diverse needs. Also, quality and accessibility is very important with ARAMARK's retail outlets.ARAMARK'S MARKETING VARIABLESWe would recommend ARAMARK to use demographic segmentation. This allows each product to be segments to either age (workers vs. college students), gender (male vs. female), or income (different prices). This will create a larger segmentation group for customers and will generate more revenue. ARAMARK'S MARKETING STRATEGY- Differentiated ARAMARK provides services in nearly every industry.  Therefore, they market to several different segments with a marketing mix strategy matched specifically to their desires and expectations.   SEGMENTATION, TARGETING AND POSITIONINGPOSITIONING MAPTARGET MARKET SEGMENT: Sports ArenasCOMPETING BRANDS: Compass group Sodexo,Cintus CorporationATTRIBUTES USED BY BUYERS IN THE SEGMENT TO UNDERSTAND BRANDS:  QualityReputation PriceNutrition Taste CintasFUNDAMENTAL WAY TO POSITION THE PRODUCT:Flexibilities of servicesHigh qualityDiverse advertising for different productsCustomer satisfactionDIMENSIONS TO POSITION ARAMARK'S BRANDS:Community Service Good will Flexibility ARAMARK could conduct secondary research on location, income for students, overweight issues, and nutritional needs in order to pin-point what the consumer needs and wants were in order to be successful.In regards to perception, different consumers will think of the products differently. Depending on the consumers personal taste, they will think of ARAMARK in multiple ways. Source used for the majority of this reasearch: www.aramark.com Multiple servicesIndustry leadershipARAMARK**POSITIONING MAPSodexoCompassBrand Management & Product Decisions Brand Strategy Branding is very important to ARAMARK. Their branding is strong relative to ARAMARK's competitors. This is because ARAMARK focuses on making sure they teach the customers about the differences of the products, services, and venues. They have a gallery full of their successes and up to date news on the company. ARAMARK connects with customers and teaches them about what they do. With this manufacturer brand name, it allows customers to see ARAMARK as all of those branding values listed above. Not all of their competitors can say that. Brand Equity BRAND AWARENESS: very large organization with lots of advertising. BRAND LOYALTY: They sell to large schools and other companies that keep coming back. They are very aware of the satisfaction of the customers. PERCEIVED QUALITY: The objects have low prices for a bulk amount. They also receive many different types of products. BRAND ASSOCIATIONS: ARAMARK explains products to customers. Many different products are made for the customer that increase positive attitudes. COMPETITIVE ADVANTAGE: ARAMARK is a large company with well-known names, so they are respected. ARAMARK suffering from trademarks and recommendation The only issue about the trademark at ARAMARK is due to having so many different products. The customers do associate ARAMARK with one or two products, but not with the many that they offer. Joint marketing could be related to ARAMARK food selection by giving out a free Betty Crocker cookie with every meal. Organizational Benefits from brand equityGoods, Services And Nonprofit Goods and Services ALMOST PURE GOODS: meals and clothing GOODS WITH SERVICES: catering, baseball game food, and uniforms with rental servicesHALF GOODS, HALF SERVICES: vending machines and cafeteria meals SERVICES WITH GOODS: training, unique software for products, and electronic mail ALMOST PURE SERVICES: health care, Human resources, legal, senior living for employers Marketing Strategy: Experience Quality ARAMARK consumers evaluate the experience qualities by experiencing the product first hand and revenues. ARAMARK provides their products in many different kinds of industries. With the multiple industries, the customers will see if they like the product to decide if they should order more from the company. ARAMARK can go to many colleges, businesses, sporting events, senior institutions, conference rooms, and industry factors. With this large selection of different industries, they allow the customers to experience the quality of their services at these places. Product Innovation And Management Product Planning/ Innovation Strategy:Marking DevelopmentNew Product Development Because ARAMARK provides services in nearly every industry, they are always looking to expand the number of industries that they serve globally, and the number of products that they introduce within those industries. Continuous Innovation example: Dining and Culinary Innovation - ARAMARK offers customized food service solutions to meet all tastes and customers.Dynamically Continuous Innovation example: Clinical Asset Tracking - Efficient tracking of clinical equipment through wireless or other new technology that people need to adapt to.Discontinuous Innovation example: ARAMARK recently launched a new brand called ARAMARK Healthcare Technologies to better design programs and service offerings that support health systems, hospitals, and clinical care facilities in maintaining clinical technologies to diagnose and treat patients.Integrated Marketing Communications Integrated Marketing Communication Objectives ARAMARK's primary objectives are to communicate value, communicate product uniqueness, and build relationships and loyalty.  This is clearly evidenced in ARAMARK's "Insight to Impact" campaign in the sports and entertainment industry. They communicate value and product uniqueness by being insightful, striving to become recognized as world-class in gathering data that predicts guest behaviors, and stays ahead of partner needs, which is also helping to build a relationship.  They establish strong relationships with their guests and take risks to improve their guests' experiences.   Integrated Marketing Communication Campaign On Aramark.com' s front page, there are several pictures with text and awards they have won, for example, Fortune World's admired companies 2013, Best employers 2013, and 2013 World's most ethical companies, which showed that ARAMARK is a highly responsible company. Mass Communications: Advertising, Sales Promotion, and Public Relations Types of Mass Communication ActivitiesSALES PROMOTION (1 low degree- 10 high degree): Online coupons-Degree (1-10): 3ADVERTISING: Ads on Youtube and commercials-Degree (1-10): 9PUBLIC RELATIONS:  Building communities, support neighborhood-Degree (1-10): 8Media Options for ARAMARKSCALE IS 1-10 (1 low importance, 10 high importance) Newspaper: 5Television: 9Radio: 5Magazines: 7Outdoor Ads: 2Internet: 10Social Media: 10Mobile: 6Personal Selling Personal Selling: ARAMARK is using both direct sales and missionary sales.DIRECT SALES: ARAMARK has some salespeople who introduce their services or uniforms to its customers directly.MISSIONARY SALES: Our customers may recommend ARAMARK to other companies, schools, or hospitals.Type of salespeople ARAMARK is involved with:Inside Sales Support: Phone calls to make sales and help customersField Salesperson : Providing food serviceTechnical Salesperson : Equipment MaintenanceService Salesperson: People who sell intangible products like cleaning servicesRoles and Responsibilities of SalespeopleAll group members tried to call/ e-mail ARAMARK, but sadly no one replied back or could direct us to people that could answer the types of questions we wanted answered. Pricing Objectives and Strategies Pricing Sensitivity ARAMARK's products have a medium (7) price sensitivity. Their goods are price sensitive, but they also have services. Services aren't as price sensitive because the customer will be willing to pay more to make sure the job gets done right. Once they purchase the service, they can't give it back. Pricing Strategies: Value-based and Cost-basedARAMARK uses cost-based pricing so they can meet the demands of their suppliers, namely Boar's Head food products. If they increase their prices nationally, ARAMARK has to comply. However, ARAMARK does try to use value-based pricing as well to meet customer demands. Understanding the customer in the food service industry is crucial.Customer Value Proposition: Operational Excellence From "The Big Three" (Sodexo, Compass Group, and ARAMARK), ARAMARK is the smallest company so they don't strive for product leadership. It is also difficult to strive for customer intimacy when you operate on a global scale. ARAMARK strives for operational excellence so they can give their customers what they want at the lowest possible price. They translate their client's needs and expectations into consistently superior results. ARAMARK builds and benefits from brand equity by making sure the customers are fully aware of the products they  sell (awareness). This leads to the customers being satisfied and becoming more loyal and returning (loyalty). Due to the bulk in quality of the products, customers receive large amounts of products for a low price. All of these aspects allow ARAMARK to be very successful and benefit them over competitors. ARAMARK's dominate planning/innovation strategy is Market Development.  They provide goods and services in nearly every industry, and they continue to try to provide services in even more markets.Introduction Phase:-ARAMARK Healthcare Technologies-Energy ManagementGrowth Phase: -Food Service and Refreshments-Clinical Technology and Services Maturity Phase: -Uniforms and Work Apparel-Facilities ManagementDecline Phase: -College catering Product life Cycle Curve1 low degree- 10 high degree: 7Example of ARAMARK advertisement: Additional Internet exampleshttps://www.facebook.com/Aramarkhttp://www.aramarkentertainment.com/http://www.aramarkrefreshments.com/webstore/Full transcriptMore presentations by
    
        
